revision.text:
'''Abortion in Cape Verde''' is legal upon request prior to 12 weeks [[gestation]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3LALpdV0DPoC&pg=PA87&dq=abortion+in+cape+verde&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiswcXZg6XSAhUB-2MKHQhkAeIQ6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=abortion%20in%20cape%20verde&f=false|title=Abortion Policies: Afghanistan to France|last=Division|first=United Nations Dept of Economic and Social Affairs Population|date=2001-01-01|publisher=United Nations Publications|isbn=9789211513516|language=en}}</ref> After 12 weeks, a woman in [[Cape Verde]] can get legal [[abortion]] care if the pregnancy poses a risk to her physical or mental health or if the fetus is impaired.<ref name=":0" /> Cape Verde is one of only four countries in Africa to permit elective abortions, alongside [[Abortion in Mozambique|Mozambique]], [[Abortion in South Africa|South Africa]], and [[Abortion in Tunisia|Tunisia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.guttmacher.org/fact-sheet/facts-abortion-africa|title=Abortion in Africa|date=2016-05-10|newspaper=Guttmacher Institute|access-date=2017-02-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/12/15/africas-abortion-wars/?_r=0|title=Africa's Abortion Wars|last=Okeowo|first=Alexis|date=|newspaper=New York Times|access-date=2017-02-23|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|work=|language=en|via=}}</ref>

== Mexico City policy ==
On January 23, 2017, [[Donald Trump]] reinstated the [[Mexico City policy]], a gag order that bans funding to American NGOs who perform, promote, or mention abortion as a [[family planning]] option.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/23/world/trump-ban-foreign-aid-abortions.html|title=Trump Revives Ban on Foreign Aid to Groups That Give Abortion Counseling|last=Sengupta|first=Somini|date=2017-01-23|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2017-02-23|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Some experts project this policy will cause 6.5 million unintended pregnancies, 2.1 million unsafe abortions, and 21,700 maternal deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/23/politics/trump-mexico-city-policy/index.html|title=Trump reverses abortion policy for aid to NGOs|last=CNN|first=Laura Koran and James Masters|website=CNN|access-date=2017-02-23}}</ref>

In response to the funding shortfall this will cause, particularly for women in developing countries, Cape Verde joined seven other nations in an initiative to raise funds for [[women's health]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-abortion-europe-idUSKBN15O0H7|title=Eight countries sign up to counter Trump's global anti-abortion move|date=2017-02-09|newspaper=Reuters|access-date=2017-02-23}}</ref>

